annotation.TEXT: Gotta make Chuck shut up... (Not that it matters, since any future RVFs in this area will be awake and chasing me as soon as they appear now, regardless of whether I silence the Chuck or not.)
Again, what did I just say about having less barf this time?
For some reason, I have a much harder time doing the P-switch recycling glitch underwater, possibly because of my reduced speed.
Heh. This level's name is "Ice to meet you". Very punny. I'm guessing that'll be an ice level. However, I've still got unfinished business back in Normal Man! to take care of first.
BGM: Yakety Sax

Now this room is the reason that other movie file went on for so long. I had made so many silly mistakes in this room, getting knocked off Yoshi several times, and just simply barfing a number of jumps.
Hello, and welcome back to... (in a creepy tone) theee Islaaand offf Insaaanityyy!!! Mwahahaha!!!
Alright, so now it's "Time to swim". Let's see what's different here, if anything...

Hi, Yoshi! Huh, I just thought of something. This is the only place where you can get Yoshi in this hack, and that requires a player to know/guess/brute force the "712" path in Spooky house, and that's only if they're aware that there's a second exit there.
...Or maybe not...
Demo count: 2?
Oh, wow! He actually powered up! This might be interesting!
And that was a very easy to collect Yoshi coin.
Look at that lone OMNOMNOM-er over here. Here, you wanna taste Yoshi's shoes? No? Well, you're not getting anything else from me!
Mario obviously wants out of this level, but since there's no side exit, his only option is suicide. (Or completing the level, but do you honestly expect that to happen?)
Demo count: 1?
Let's try to speed run this place so Yoshi won't have time to swallow the key!
And I'm through this room (which doesn't appear to have changed at all) far faster than the the previous time!
I just love watching that koopa dance down the slope!
But then he chooses death by chocolate. Nuts.
And now it's back to Ice to meet you.
Demo count: 8?
"Ice to meet you", too!
Well, I guess next time, I'll be exploring Some Lake!
Still more sprite slot disagreement. Oh, well. I'll just wait for Yoshi to swallow and then slurp up the key.
There's that goal-Rex-in-a-box, just like last time.
And then he gets indecisive about that jump!
Umm... I'm wondering why I even bothered with that Yoshi coin now, since I'm planning to get this level's secret exit first anyway.
Alright, so this is one of those new levels. Let me translate the name here...
Yep, I even got out of the Yoshi coin area like that.
Double gulp!
Everything seems to be the same here, including the unreachable moons... Wait...
Are you going back to Normal Man! for real now?
I didn't take any damage while off of Yoshi, but I did almost run out of time. However, I did make it to the end and clear the level.
And here's Normal Man! The most ordinary hero of them all!
A mushroom? Nah, I think I'd rather have my two flowers.
Not that it matters, since there's still no way to reach them. But at least now I know I'm not missing out on the real deals!
Well, he made it farther than I expected.
There's another fake ? block.
What did I just say about having less barf this time?
Now, this time around, I'm not going to try mimicking those follies, and instead, I'll try to get up this room in a more competent manner.
That was an odd "Hurry Up!" sound...
I'll try to mimic some of what I had done the first time around. For instance, I failed to block clone this block just like that.
Man, he can't seem to make up his mind now!
Now let's play this level for realsies! (Or is that spelled "realzies"?)
Not really much to say here, except maybe the emptier parts of the level could use more enemies or objects to make them a bit more interesting.

Man, maybe ZSNES's movie recording function just doesn't seem to like Island of Insanity V4, much like how it doesn't like Magical Drop 2. Regardless, I'm still going to keep using ZSNES, because I'm more comfortable with it, and it does generally work correctly about 95% of the time.
Ow! No, that was not a ZSNES desync. I really did barf badly there. Good thing for Start+Select!
Yep, now let's see if the second half of the level is any different.
Yeah, that level appeared to be completely unchanged. Maybe I should've sped up the footage of that level since there was nothing new? What do you guys think?
Demo count: 4?
Demo count: 9?
BARF!
To be continued...
Demo count: 10?

...Actually, that time was indeed a ZSNES desync... There's no way I'd miss a simple jump like that and not react with a quick Start+Select! Well, I guess I should insert some appropriate music while we watch the barfy mess that ZSNES created!
Demo count: 7?
Demo count: 6?
Now, since I mentioned two episodes ago that I generally do just one level per movie file, you're probably wondering why this desync is still going on. Well, I'll explain later.
There's that key that requires Yoshi again.
Eh, ehh! I'm trying to pass through this block here for no reason... Maybe if I try from the other side...
He's trying Normal Man! again...
Ah, good. I actually managed to get stars this time! 40 feels good after completely missing the previous two times!

And of course, I took a hit just as I was saying that last sentence, but I recovered immediately, so I'm still doing far better than the previous time! Also, I almost take a bullet to the brain here, but it doesn't actually hit me, so I'm still good.
Yeah, I don't think the sprite slots will ever cooperate with me here. Bye, Yoshi!
Oh, no! It's a Kaizo trap! ...Not! The edge of the screen protects me here.
Awesome!
And there's my secret exit.
And then I did go for this Yoshi coin from this side like this.
And another.
Okay, that worked. There was no point in me doing that except to be random.
Also, I guess we get a sneak peek at the next level, which is indeed an ice level.
And now I've unlocked... Let me just translate this... "Some Lake". Haha.
And actually, I'm going to go back to GET OUT! real quick to get myself another Yoshi.
So, the normal exit there unlocked "Our last challenge" as usual. However, I'm going to head on over to that new level, because I want to show off something brand new in this episode!
Okay, I'm back to the point just before the desync made me jump in the pit the first time here.
Everything seems the same so far...
It's a fake ? block. You can tell because it's backwards (like those moons in Normal Man!), and I pass right through it when I try to hit it.
Demo count: 0
Whoa, that was kind of lucky. Also, there's that slope-dancing koopa again!
Ooh, he smashed the koopa and almost made it to the Yoshi coin!
Gulp!
No, Yoshi, don't swallow the-- Gulp! ...key...
Oh, looks like he's heading back to Normal Man! now...
Another phony.
Those moons are backwards! That means they're phonies! Total phonies!
Let's try this again, with less barf this time!
That was cool. Unnecessary, but cool.
And now it's back to Ice to meet you again.
Bah! I thought I'd make it under that Urchin without getting hit. Well, no worry, since there should be a pipe up ahead that Yoshi will bounce off of.

Nuts. Missed the goal tape. However, this time, that miss was intentional, because I missed it that exact same way the previous time, and I was like, "Wow, did I really just miss the goal tape a second time in a row?".
I'm sure this key is important, since this is a red level.
...Or maybe yes...
BGM: Jazz Jackrabbit - Tubelectric

On top of that, the key to the secret exit in Normal Man! requires Yoshi to reach, so a whole bunch of levels are unavailable to those who don't take the "712" path in Spooky house. Maybe there should be a hint towards Spooky house's secret exit, perhaps as a message box near Normal Man!'s key.
This all seems to be the same, and this pipe still doesn't go anywhere.

And now the next movie file begins, and there's no more desync from this point on for the rest of this episode. (Note: My score and coins when I begin the next level will be different than what you just saw.)
Yes, those paragoombas love to ambush you here, and that accounted for a few of my stumbles last time.
Man, you can tell that even that koopa is confused about what's going on with Mario!
That unlocks "LEAVE!", which I'm not going to do right now. However, I will go back for Ice to meet you's secret exit, and try not to swallow the key this time!
...or not.
Okay, Ice to meet you it is!
Demo count: 5?
Whoops! Well, I just missed a whole coin trail, but I can always Yoshi jump back up to try again at it.
Demo count: 3?
Oh, and the keyhole was right here too... This would normally have been a no-brainer of a secret exit. Oh, well. I'd have to play the level twice anyway.
Pfft. Well, that's a goal tape miss.
Well. That happened.

And that's it. The desynched movie file ends with Mario just standing on the overworld here for several seconds. I guess I'll turn off the Yakety Sax now and do the usual game crash intermission screen while I fix things up...
Around here, I had spit the key into the pit to my left. I didn't do that this time, but whatever. I don't have any use for the key now anyway, so it doesn't matter.
